definitions.definition: A person who sets up a business; generally, a person who owns and manages a business and assumes its financial risks.
A person who organizes concerts , plays , or other entertainments ; the manager of a theatre or similar venue; an impresario .
A person who serves as an intermediary; a middleman ; a go-between .
A person who manages an artist or performer ; an agent .

main_definition: A person who sets up a business; generally, a person who owns and manages a business and assumes its financial risks. [from 1762]
secondary_definitions: ( now rare ) A person who organizes concerts , plays , or other entertainments ; the manager of a theatre or similar venue; an impresario . [from 1800]
( rare , sometimes figurative ) A person who serves as an intermediary; a middleman ; a go-between .
( obsolete ) A person who manages an artist or performer ; an agent . [1851–1887]
